9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 13, L.D. 4, “An Act to Adopt Eastern
10 Standard Time Year-round”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §151 by inserting after subsection 3 the following:
12 '4. Effective date. Year-round eastern standard time under subsection 1 takes effect
13 at 2 a.m. on the 2nd Sunday of March 2026.'
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, sets an effective date
1188 for the adoption of year-round eastern standard time.
